<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>About Daily Story</h1>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>What is Daily Story?</h2>
            <p>Daily Story helps you practice reading in your target language with AI-generated content tailored to your skill level. Get a new story every day in 8 different languages!</p>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>How It Works</h2>
            <ol class="how-to-list">
                <li><strong>Choose your language</strong> - Select from English, Spanish, French, German, Italian, Portuguese, Chinese, or Japanese</li>
                <li><strong>Pick your level</strong> - Select A1, A2, B1, or B2 based on your reading ability</li>
                <li><strong>Read & quiz</strong> - Read today's story and test your comprehension with 3 questions</li>
                <li><strong>Come back daily</strong> - Bookmark your level and return each day for fresh content</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Understanding CEFR Levels</h2>
            <p class="cefr-intro">The Common European Framework of Reference (CEFR) is a standard for measuring language ability. Here's what each level means:</p>

            <div class="level-description">
                <h3>A1 - Beginner</h3>
                <p class="level-subtitle">You can understand simple conversations with everyday phrases and basic vocabulary.</p>
                <p><strong>Examples:</strong> Ordering food, asking directions, greeting friends</p>
            </div>

            <div class="level-description">
                <h3>A2 - Elementary</h3>
                <p class="level-subtitle">You can understand short conversations about familiar topics with common expressions.</p>
                <p><strong>Examples:</strong> Making plans, talking about hobbies, simple descriptions</p>
            </div>

            <div class="level-description">
                <h3>B1 - Intermediate</h3>
                <p class="level-subtitle">You can understand conversations about everyday and moderately complex topics.</p>
                <p><strong>Examples:</strong> Debates, discussions, professional emails, opinion exchanges</p>
            </div>

            <div class="level-description">
                <h3>B2 - Upper Intermediate</h3>
                <p class="level-subtitle">You can understand in-depth discussions on concrete and abstract topics with nuanced language.</p>
                <p><strong>Examples:</strong> Work discussions, analytical debates, detailed explanations</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Tips for Best Results</h2>
            <ul class="tips-list">
                <li>Start one level below where you think you are - it's better to build confidence</li>
                <li>Don't worry about understanding every word - focus on getting the main idea</li>
                <li>Use the quiz to check your comprehension, not just vocabulary</li>
                <li>Read daily for consistent practice - even 5 minutes counts!</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Open Source</h2>
            <p>Daily Story is open source! Check out the code, contribute, or report issues on <a href="https://github.com/appdevjohn/daily-story" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.</p>
        </section>

